/*! \page changes Changes

\ref libhd_5_12

<hr>

\subsection libhd_5_12 Changes in libhd-5.12

There have been some changes to libhd's interface:

<ul>

  <li>changes in \ref hd_t

    <ul>

    <li>\ref hd_t::bus is now a struct, use bus.id instead

    <li>\ref hd_t::base_class is now a struct, use base_class.id instead

    <li>\ref hd_t::sub_class is now a struct, use sub_class.id instead

    <li>\ref hd_t::prog_if is now a struct, use prog_if.id instead

    <li>\ref hd_t::vendor is a struct replacing vend and vend_name.
      Use vendor.id and vendor.name now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::device is a struct replacing dev and dev_name.
      Use device.id and device.name now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::sub_vendor is a struct replacing sub_vend and sub_vend_name.
      Use sub_vendor.id and sub_vendor.name now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::sub_device is a struct replacing sub_dev and sub_dev_name.
      Use sub_device.id and sub_device.name now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::revision is a struct replacing rev and rev_name.
      Use revision.id and revision.name now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::compat_vendor is a struct replacing compat_vend.
      Use compat_vendor.id now.

    <li>\ref hd_t::compat_device is a struct replacing compat_dev.
      Use compat_device.id now.

    </ul>

  <li>interface functions removed

    <ul>

    <li>hd_bus_name is gone. Use hd_t::bus.name instead.

    <li>hd_class_name is gone. Use hd_t::base_class.name,
      hd_t::sub_class.name or hd_t::prog_if.name instead.

    <li>hd_vendor_name is gone. Use hd_t::vendor.name instead.

    <li>hd_device_name is gone. Use hd_t::device.name instead.

    <li>hd_sub_device_name is gone. Use hd_t::sub_device.name instead.

    <li>hd_find_device_by_name is gone.

    </ul>

</ul>

<hr>

*/

